    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Dataset exploration and preprocessing\n",
        "prepared by Blake Mires"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "gtn_wDOKsFDk"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Libraries**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kJtOOghABQZx"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7tPeVgWzBJ6l"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# os is used to work with files and folders\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "# urllib.request downloads the dataset from the internet\n",
        "import urllib.request\n",
        "\n",
        "# zipfile extracts the downloaded ZIP file\n",
        "import zipfile\n",
        "\n",
        "# pandas is used to load, clean, and analyze the data\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "# matplotlib is used to create charts\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Dataset**\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset is downloaded from the official GroupLens website."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1Yn4jt-IBYgj"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# official MovieLens 100K dataset URL\n",
        "\n",
        "dataset_url = (\n",
        "    \"https://files.grouplens.org/\"\n",
        "    \"datasets/movielens/ml-100k.zip\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "zip_file = \"/content/ml-100k.zip\"\n",
        "data_folder = \"/content/ml-100k\"\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# download the dataset if it is not already available\n",
        "\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(zip_file):\n",
        "    print(\"Downloading the dataset...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    urllib.request.urlretrieve(\n",
        "        dataset_url,\n",
        "        zip_file\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(\"Download complete.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"The ZIP file already exists.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# extract the dataset if it has not already been extracted\n",
        "\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(data_folder):\n",
        "    print(\"Extracting the dataset...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    with zipfile.ZipFile(zip_file, \"r\") as zip_reference:\n",
        "        zip_reference.extractall(\"/content\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(\"Extraction complete.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"The dataset folder already exists.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "ghOyK3P4BdUZ",
        "outputId": "69c5c651-2103-4753-83d1-616f6ae06d6e"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "The ZIP file already exists.\n",
            "The dataset folder already exists.\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Load rating data**\n",
        "\n",
        "According to the MovieLens README, the u.data file contains four fields in this order:\n",
        "\n",
        "User ID\n",
        "Item ID\n",
        "Rating\n",
        "Timestamp\n",
        "\n",
        "The file does not contain column headings, so the names are assigned when it is loaded.\n",
        "\n",
        "The values are separated by tabs, which is why sep=\"\\t\" is used."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ByFwcIdMIH9G"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# column order provided by the MovieLens README\n",
        "rating_columns = [\n",
        "    \"user_id\",\n",
        "    \"item_id\",\n",
        "    \"rating\",\n",
        "    \"timestamp\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# load the ratings file into a pandas DataFrame\n",
        "ratings = pd.read_csv(\n",
        "    \"/content/ml-100k/u.data\",\n",
        "    sep=\"\\t\",\n",
        "    names=rating_columns\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# show the first five rows\n",
        "ratings.head()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 206
