    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Bar chart results**\n",
        "\n",
        "Most ratings were positive. A 4 was the most common, followed by 3 and then 5. Ratings of 1 and 2 were less frequent, so users generally rated the movies favorably."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kORMo7jdjjIh"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# visualize the number of ratings submitted per user\n",
        "# group the records by user and count each user's ratings\n",
        "ratings_per_user = (\n",
        "    data\n",
        "    .groupby(\"user_id\")\n",
        "    .size()\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# show summary statistics for ratings submitted per user\n",
        "print(\"Summary of ratings submitted per user:\")\n",
        "print(ratings_per_user.describe())\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# make a chart that is eight inches wide and five inches tall\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# make a histogram using 30 intervals\n",
        "plt.hist(\n",
        "    ratings_per_user,\n",
        "    bins=30\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# add a title describing the chart\n",
        "plt.title(\"Number of Ratings Submitted per User\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# label the horizontal axis\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Number of Ratings\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# label the vertical axis\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Number of Users\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# show the completed chart\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 661
        },
        "id": "Z8aQ3VLeSvoF",
