    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Histogram of ratings per movie results**\n",
        "\n",
        "Most movies only got a few ratings, while a small number received several hundred. This made another right-skewed distribution with a long tail toward the most frequently rated movies."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lu5gawUAkY8K"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# movie-rating summary\n",
        "\n",
        "# group the data by item ID and movie title\n",
        "movie_summary = (\n",
        "    data\n",
        "    .groupby(\n",
        "        [\"item_id\", \"title\"],\n",
        "        as_index=False\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    .agg(\n",
        "        # count the number of ratings received by each movie\n",
        "        number_of_ratings=(\"rating\", \"count\"),\n",
        "\n",
        "        # calculate the average rating for each movie\n",
        "        average_rating=(\"rating\", \"mean\")\n",
        "    )\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# round each average rating to two decimal places\n",
        "movie_summary[\"average_rating\"] = (\n",
        "    movie_summary[\"average_rating\"].round(2)\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# display the first five movie-summary records\n",
        "movie_summary.head()"
      ],
